Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last Update: DEC-2004
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from any ISO-92 compliant database to a DB2 UDB database using the native LOAD Command. - This module uses Sunopsis Command SnpsSqlUnload to extract data in a temporary file. Data is then loaded in the target temporary DB2 table created dynamically using the LOAD CLP command. - When using this module on a journalized source table, the journal table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface.
Restrictions: - The IBM DB2 Command Line Processor (CLP) as well as the IBM DB2 Connect Software must be installed on the machine running the Sunopsis Agent. - The IBM DB2 UDB technology must be updated in the Sunopsis Topology: The "Using Data Server" check box must be checked. - The target DB2 Database Name must be entered in the "Data Server" field of the target IBM DB2 Data Server declared in Sunopsis Topology. - The user specified in the IBM DB2 Data Server in the Sunopsis Topology must have enough privileges to run the LOAD utility (this can be achieved with a GRANT LOAD ON DATABASE statement). - The temporary data file format is delimited by tabs (Hexadecimal character 0x09) - The default timestamp format in the temporary datafile is YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS - Specify appropriate options values according to their description.
Call command to execute a shell
Enter the name of the command shell specific processor. Examples: - On Windows: DB2CMD /c /w OR cmd.exe /c - On Unix / Linux: sh -c OR db2cmd -c -w
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

Additional options used when creating the C$ temporary table. You may use this option if you wish to create the temporary table in a nologging mode (transaction is not written to the DB2 log files) or if you wish to specify a tablespace name. Examples: - Disable logging: NOT LOGGED INITIALLY - Specify a tablespace: IN MY_TABLESPACE NOT LOGGED INITIALLY - Compress Values: VALUE COMPRESSION
Temp. Directory for the data file

Directory where the temporary data file is created. This directory must be a valid path on the machine running the Sunopsis Agent. Examples: - On Windows: D:\MyDatafiles\MyTemporaryFolder - On Unix / Linux: /usr/tmp
